---
<Layout
  title="Decision provenance"
  description="How the OPDA PDTF ontology was built and ratified — the term-level dct:source contract, the ODR/ADR/council lineage that governs each layer, programme retirement and reconciliation, and the records governing this reference itself."
>
<PageMeta category="Ontology" variant="brand" updated="Draft · Updated 2026-06-14" />

  <h1>Decision provenance</h1>

  <p class="lead">
    Every term in the OPDA PDTF ontology traces back to a source, and every modelling
    decision traces back to a ratified record. This page is the audit trail: how the
    ontology was built from the PDTF schemas, how each layer was decided through the
    Linked Data Council, and which records govern this reference document itself. A
    completeness claim that hides where a term came from is a provenance lie — so the
    chain is laid out explicitly here.
  </p>

  <nav class="callout callout--note" aria-label="On this page">
    <div class="callout__label">On this page</div>
    <ul style="margin: 0;">
      <li><a href="#term-provenance">Term-level provenance — the <code>dct:source</code> contract</a></li>
      <li><a href="#lineage">The ODR / ADR / council lineage</a></li>
      <li><a href="#retirement">Programme retirement &amp; reconciliation</a></li>
      <li><a href="#this-reference">Records governing this reference</a></li>
      <li><a href="#dissents">Held-as-live dissents</a></li>
    </ul>
  </nav>

  <h2 id="term-provenance">Term-level provenance — the <code>dct:source</code> contract</h2>
  <p>
    The foundational rule (<a href="/modelling/odr/odr-0004">ODR-0004</a>, PDTF Ontology
    Foundation) is that <strong>every term carries a <code>dct:source</code></strong> that
    resolves to where it came from — a PDTF schema leaf path (a JSON pointer into the
    overlay schemas) or a business-glossary row. No term is invented free-floating; if it
    exists in the ontology, it can be walked back to a PDTF artefact or a curated OPDA
    glossary entry. This is what lets the reference claim it is <em>generated from</em> the
    schemas rather than hand-waved alongside them.
  </p>
  <p>
    The same contract underpins the overlay profiles: a form's profile binds Category-G
    leaves as per-leaf <code>sh:path</code> shapes, and every other leaf is carried by
    <code>dct:subject</code> plus a JSON-pointer <code>dct:source</code> and entered in the
    gap register — never silently dropped, never fabricated. Provenance is therefore not a
    decorative annotation; it is the mechanism by which the gap register stays honest (see
    <a href="/ontology/known-issues">Known issues</a> for the thin-profile consequence).
  </p>

  <h2 id="lineage">The ODR / ADR / council lineage</h2>
  <p>
    The ontology was not designed in one pass. Each layer was decided as an Ontology
    Decision Record (ODR), most of them adjudicated by the Linked Data Council (the
    dialectic expert panel, methodology in <a href="/modelling/odr/odr-0001">ODR-0001</a>).
    The records below are the governing decisions, layer by layer; each links to its live
    record in the <a href="/modelling/odr">ODR corpus</a>.
  </p>

  <table>
    <thead><tr><th>Layer</th><th>Governing record</th><th>What it decided</th></tr></thead>
    <tbody>
      <tr><td>Languages &amp; vocabularies</td><td><a href="/modelling/odr/odr-0002">ODR-0002</a></td><td>OWL 2 + SHACL + SKOS + PROV-O + DPV; the adopted stack.</td></tr>
      <tr><td>Foundation</td><td><a href="/modelling/odr/odr-0004">ODR-0004</a></td><td>Three-graph separation, the <code>dct:source</code> contract, namespace policy.</td></tr>
      <tr><td>Identity crux</td><td><a href="/modelling/odr/odr-0005">ODR-0005</a></td><td>Property / LegalEstate / RegisteredTitle split; UPRN as a Quality, never the identity criterion.</td></tr>
      <tr><td>Agents &amp; roles</td><td><a href="/modelling/odr/odr-0006">ODR-0006</a></td><td>Roles are anti-rigid, keyed by their founding Relator, never a subclass of a Kind.</td></tr>
      <tr><td>Transactions &amp; lifecycle</td><td><a href="/modelling/odr/odr-0007">ODR-0007</a></td><td>Transaction as a Relator founding Seller/Buyer roles.</td></tr>
      <tr><td>Claims, evidence &amp; provenance</td><td><a href="/modelling/odr/odr-0009">ODR-0009</a></td><td>PROV-O backing; three truth-makers — derivation, signature, assurance.</td></tr>
      <tr><td>Overlay-profile mechanism</td><td><a href="/modelling/odr/odr-0010">ODR-0010</a></td><td>"A form IS its SHACL overlay" — the per-leaf binding pattern.</td></tr>
      <tr><td>Enumeration vocabularies</td><td><a href="/modelling/odr/odr-0011">ODR-0011</a></td><td>Coded values as SKOS concept schemes.</td></tr>
      <tr><td>Data-governance layer</td><td><a href="/modelling/odr/odr-0012">ODR-0012</a></td><td>DPV referenced-not-imported; class-level co-annotation.</td></tr>
      <tr><td>SHACL validation &amp; severity</td><td><a href="/modelling/odr/odr-0013">ODR-0013</a></td><td>Severity tiers; profile-emission rules.</td></tr>
      <tr><td>SHACL-AF data-quality rules</td><td><a href="/modelling/odr/odr-0017">ODR-0017</a></td><td>Non-blocking advanced rules; requires <code>advanced=True</code> validation.</td></tr>
      <tr><td>DPV co-annotation pattern</td><td><a href="/modelling/odr/odr-0018">ODR-0018</a></td><td>Personal-data categories annotated, not asserted as subclasses.</td></tr>
      <tr><td>Entailment regime</td><td><a href="/modelling/odr/odr-0025">ODR-0025</a></td><td>Inference semantics; domain/range rules deliberately excluded from the safe closure.</td></tr>
      <tr><td>Safe ruleset adoption</td><td><a href="/modelling/odr/odr-0026">ODR-0026</a></td><td>The OWL-RL-safe ruleset; unevaluated modelling axioms held as a boundary.</td></tr>
      <tr><td>Classification doctrine</td><td><a href="/modelling/odr/odr-0027">ODR-0027</a></td><td>Facets via SKOS over subclass trees; <code>isMemberOf</code> as the default.</td></tr>
    </tbody>
  </table>

  <h2 id="retirement">Programme retirement &amp; reconciliation</h2>
  <p>
    The PDTF-to-ontology build was run as a time-boxed programme, and that programme is
    now closed. The retirement is itself recorded, so the reference is honest about being a
    historical anchor rather than an open work item:
  </p>
  <ul>
    <li>
      <strong>Programme RETIRED 2026-06-14.</strong> The work-breakdown programme record
      (<a href="/modelling/odr/odr-0003">ODR-0003</a>, PDTF to Ontology: Programme and Work
      Breakdown) is retired. Modelling continues under fresh ODRs, but the original
      programme structure no longer governs new work.
    </li>
    <li>
      <strong>Descriptive layer reconciled complete</strong> (<a href="/modelling/odr/odr-0028">ODR-0028</a>,
      Descriptive-Layer Completeness Reconciliation). The descriptive attribute binning was
      reconciled against the schemas; the emitted TTL is correct G-grade (a residual
      Category-C over-count is a report-side miscount, not an emitted defect).
    </li>
    <li>
      <strong>VC / DID compatibility waived.</strong> The Verifiable Credentials / DID
      compatibility layer (<a href="/modelling/odr/odr-0016">ODR-0016</a>) is held as
      proposed and waived for this cut — claims provenance is delivered through PROV-O
      (ODR-0009), not a VC envelope, in the current reference.
    </li>
  </ul>

  <h2 id="this-reference">Records governing this reference</h2>
  <p>
    This <code>/ontology</code> section is itself the product of decisions, taken in two
    later Council sessions and a rename ADR:
  </p>
  <ul>
    <li>
      <strong>ADR-0041 (session-038) — this reference is the generation model.</strong>
      The Ontology Reference Document decision: <code>/ontology</code> is the published,
      authoritative reference, generated from the committed TTL corpus and guarded by the
      doc-drift CI gate, with the multi-tool bake-off scored per layer and the best method
      adopted into one woven reference. The decision record is in the
      <a href="/modelling/odr">ODR / ADR corpus</a>; the bake-off itself lives on the
      <a href="/ontology/bake-off">Tool bake-off</a> page.
    </li>
    <li>
      <strong>ODR-0029 (session-039) — the inference / validation boundary.</strong>
      <a href="/modelling/odr/odr-0029">ODR-0029</a> disposes of the entailment regime: infer
      the relations whose closure the author wants (the seven frozen rules — subclass,
      subproperty, inverse, symmetric, transitive and their kin); validate the constraints
      the author wants checked (domain, range, cardinality, identity) as SHACL. On the OPDA
      schema the safe closure adds <strong>0 triples</strong> over the flat asserted graph,
      so a single rendering per tool is correct (entailed ≡ asserted here).
    </li>
    <li>
      <strong>ADR-0042 — the rename.</strong> The <code>/manual</code> section was renamed
      to <code>/model</code> (the DAMA four-tier reader presentation). This reference links
      out to <a href="/model">/model</a> for the tiered reader view; the rename is recorded
      so old <code>/manual</code> references resolve to the decision.
    </li>
  </ul>

  <h2 id="dissents">Held-as-live dissents</h2>
  <p>
    Where the Council split, the dissent is recorded as live with a named re-open trigger
    rather than papered over — a decision that conceals its own contested points is not
    sound provenance. Two are carried on the record:
  </p>
  <ul>
    <li>
      <strong>Davis on <a href="/modelling/odr/odr-0009">ODR-0009</a></strong> (claims /
      evidence / provenance) — held as live; re-opens if a named consumer needs a VC-envelope
      truth-maker the PROV-O backing does not carry.
    </li>
    <li>
      <strong>Allemang on <a href="/modelling/odr/odr-0012">ODR-0012</a></strong> (the
      data-governance layer) — held as live on the referenced-not-imported DPV treatment.
    </li>
    <li>
      <strong><code>oc1</code> / <code>llc1</code> held thin</strong> — re-opens when a named
      consumer issues a worked SPARQL query against an authority-register leaf (see
      <a href="/ontology/known-issues">Known issues</a>).
    </li>
  </ul>

  <p class="muted">
    Related: <a href="/ontology/known-issues">Known issues</a> (the dated defect/caveat
    register), <a href="/ontology/usage">Consume the ontology</a> (machine access), and the
    full <a href="/modelling/odr">ODR / ADR corpus</a>.
  </p>
</Layout>
